The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call passes the address of a compound literal &(lfs_off_t){0} as the out-parameter for 'off'. In lfs_ctz_find() there is a case 'if (size == 0) { *block = LFS_BLOCK_NULL; *off = 0; return 0; }'. If file->ctz.size == 0 that assignment '*off = 0' is executed but only writes into the temporary compound literal whose value is never used by the caller, so the write has no effect on program behaviour. This constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
